To find what are considered the great- est dry wines of the world, one must look to Burgundy. We herald enthusi- astically the great ’66s—wines of fan- tastic breed, airy lightness, and extra- ordinary bouquet. Here are superb, dry whites that are genuinely ready for present drinking—not for laying down—the ’62s, if good, can be dramatically fine, rich in every quality.
